The paper deals with algorithms for space-efficient depth-first search (DFS) in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents several new algorithms and analyzes their time and space complexity. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AL (Computational Complexity), cs.CC (Computational Complexity and Cryptography), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
